WEBVTT

00:01.752 --> 00:03.214
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:03.214 --> 00:04.545
TELL HER TO GO AWAY!
 WE ARE GONNA BE A FAMILY.

00:04.545 --> 00:06.257
I FINALLY REMEMBER
WHAT I DID DURING MY BLACKOUTS.

00:06.257 --> 00:08.259
IT'S ALL BECAUSE
OF THAT ONE MEMORY.

00:08.259 --> 00:10.261
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
WHO KNEW HOW TO SAVE ME.

00:10.261 --> 00:12.473
Brooks:
YOU'VE SEEN HIM BEFORE.

00:12.473 --> 00:14.185
AND I NEVER THOUGHT I'D BE
HAPPY TO SEE HIM AGAIN.

00:14.185 --> 00:17.098
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR AN
APPRENTICE IN MY TUSCAN STUDIO.

00:17.098 --> 00:18.479
Patrick: I'VE BEEN GIVEN
AN OPPORTUNITY.

00:18.479 --> 00:19.690
BUT IT MEANS
I HAVE TO LEAVE.

00:19.690 --> 00:22.233
Goodbye, Mom.
I will always love you.

00:22.233 --> 00:25.486
PASCAL LeMARCHAL
IS ON HIS WAY FROM PARIS.

00:25.486 --> 00:27.358
RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

00:27.358 --> 00:30.030
STEVIE GRAYSON
IS MY BIOLOGICAL MOTHER.

00:30.030 --> 00:31.702
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
GIVE HER A CHANCE.

00:31.702 --> 00:34.245
I WAS IN A REHAB
WHEN I FOUND OUT I WAS PREGNANT.

00:34.245 --> 00:35.456
I COULDN'T
BE A DECENT MOTHER

00:35.456 --> 00:36.997
UNTIL I LEARNED HOW
TO TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

00:36.997 --> 00:40.791
Emily: I THINK STEVIE GRAYSON
VISITED MY FATHER IN PRISON.

00:40.791 --> 00:43.254
WHAT DO YOU THINK SHE WANTED?
 SHE CAME HERE WITH SECRETS.

00:43.254 --> 00:45.256
I'M GONNA FIND OUT
EVERY SINGLE ONE.

00:45.256 --> 00:48.259
[ MAN SINGING IN ITALIAN ]

00:51.432 --> 00:55.226
Emily: GRACE IS
 AT THE CORE OF TRAGEDY.

00:58.269 --> 01:01.142
FOR IF THERE'S NO HEIGHT
 AT WHICH TO DROP,

01:01.142 --> 01:02.853
NO PRIDE TAKEN
 IN THE LIFE LIVED,

01:02.853 --> 01:05.105
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO LOSE.

01:09.069 --> 01:13.073
BUT ONCE IN THE FREE FALL
 OF DISGRACE...

01:15.075 --> 01:18.038
...THE ONLY WAY
 TO CHANGE ITS MOMENTUM

01:18.038 --> 01:20.661
IS TO USE IT TO YOUR ADVANTAGE.

01:28.048 --> 01:31.011
I FORGOT. TOMORROW'S
THE OPENING NIGHT OF THE OPERA.

01:31.011 --> 01:33.013
MM. IT'S "PAGLIACCI."

01:33.013 --> 01:36.217
ONE OF PATRICK'S FAVORITES.
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:36.217 --> 01:38.018
I'M SORRY HE'S GONE.

01:38.018 --> 01:39.640
THANK YOU, DANIEL.

01:39.640 --> 01:44.225
MY ONLY CONSOLATION IS
THAT YOUR FATHER WON'T BE THERE.

01:44.225 --> 01:45.986
I'M SORRY EMILY WILL,
 THOUGH.

01:45.986 --> 01:48.989
WELL...

01:48.989 --> 01:50.991
MAYBE NOT.

01:50.991 --> 01:53.284
BECAUSE THAT
WAS TAKEN YESTERDAY.

01:53.284 --> 01:55.446
[ GASPS ]

01:57.658 --> 01:59.740
IT WAS MY ASSUMPTION
THAT AIDEN HAD LEFT TOWN

01:59.740 --> 02:01.502
AFTER I KICKED HIM
OUT OF THE HOUSE.

02:01.502 --> 02:03.504
WELL,
I'M GLAD HE STUCK AROUND

02:03.504 --> 02:06.126
BECAUSE I FINALLY HAVE MY TICKET
OUT OF THIS MARRIAGE.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.878
I'M JUST WAITING FOR HER
TO GET HOME.

02:07.878 --> 02:11.672
YOU KNOW, THAT'S THE FIRST SMILE
I'VE SEEN ON YOU IN A WHILE.

02:11.672 --> 02:13.844
MAY I ASK YOU A FAVOR?

02:13.844 --> 02:17.017
PLEASE GIVE ME A FRONT-ROW SEAT
WHEN YOU TELL HER.

02:21.932 --> 02:25.526
SO, YOU'RE SURE SHE ONLY
VISITED HIM THE ONE TIME?

02:25.526 --> 02:28.319
STEVIE GRAYSON,
A.K.A. STEPHANIE PRUITT,

02:28.319 --> 02:31.942
ONLY CHECKED INTO
THE VISITOR LOG ONCE -- 1997.

02:31.942 --> 02:36.277
A FEW DAYS LATER, SHE WAS BUSTED
FOR A D.U.I. AND LEFT FOR CALI.

02:38.038 --> 02:41.622
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]
THAT'S WHY I NEVER KNEW.

02:41.622 --> 02:43.414
AND NEITHER
DID MY FATHER.

02:43.414 --> 02:45.416
STEVIE USED HER MAIDEN NAME
SO HE WOULDN'T KNOW

02:45.416 --> 02:47.628
THAT SHE WAS A GRAYSON.

02:47.628 --> 02:51.252
OR SHE DIDN'T WANT CONRAD
TO KNOW THAT SHE VISITED HIM.

02:51.252 --> 02:53.093
SO THE FIRST THING
WE NEED TO FIGURE OUT

02:53.093 --> 02:54.675
IS WHOSE SIDE SHE'S ON.

02:54.675 --> 02:58.058
IF JACK'S TRYING TO WRAP HIS
HEAD AROUND HIS NEWFOUND MOM...

02:58.058 --> 02:59.760
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
...THIS IS GONNA BLOW HIS MIND.

02:59.760 --> 03:02.353
JACK STAYS OUT OF IT.
YOU KNOW THAT.

03:02.353 --> 03:04.435
WELL, THIS IS HIS MOTHER
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT.

03:04.435 --> 03:06.066
WHO I CAN
APPROACH DIRECTLY,

03:06.066 --> 03:08.018
GIVEN THAT I CALLED HER TO TOWN
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

03:08.018 --> 03:09.610
AND WHAT IF YOU
HAVE TO TAKE HER DOWN?

03:10.771 --> 03:12.112
DON'T YOU THINK
YOU'VE DONE ENOUGH TO JACK,

03:12.112 --> 03:14.865
OR ARE YOU PREPARED
TO DESTROY HIM ALL OVER AGAIN?

03:17.238 --> 03:19.240
[ SCOFFS ]
YOU'RE TESTING ME.

03:19.240 --> 03:21.872
JUST WANT TO MAKE SURE
YOU'RE NOT GONNA BLACK OUT

03:21.872 --> 03:23.914
AND BECOME
YOUR OWN WORST EMILY.

03:23.914 --> 03:25.376
BUT, SERIOUSLY,

03:25.376 --> 03:27.708
ARE YOU SURE THAT YOU DON'T
WANT TO BRING JACK INTO THIS?

03:27.708 --> 03:29.500
ABSOLUTELY NOT,

03:29.500 --> 03:33.504
ESPECIALLY SINCE I DON'T
KNOW WHAT "THIS" IS YET.

03:33.504 --> 03:36.467
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

03:36.467 --> 03:38.679
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:38.679 --> 03:42.102
I HAD NO IDEA YOUR FATHER
WAS COMING BACK WITH YOU.

03:42.102 --> 03:43.644
HE WASN'T SUPPOSED TO.

03:43.644 --> 03:46.226
WELL, HIS ARRIVAL IS
BURNING UP THE GOSSIP LINE.

03:46.226 --> 03:48.609
EVERYONE WANTS TO KNOW
WHO PASCAL LeMARCHAL

03:48.609 --> 03:50.901
WILL BRING WITH HIM
TO THE OPERA TOMORROW.

03:50.901 --> 03:52.232
HOW DO YOU WANT ME
TO HANDLE IT?

03:52.232 --> 03:54.945
[ CHUCKLES ]
THERE'S NOTHING TO HANDLE.

03:56.317 --> 03:59.320
HE'LL BE GONE
BEFORE THE CURTAIN RISES.

03:59.320 --> 04:02.623
I FLEW MARGAUX OVER
IN MY BOMBARDIER GLOBAL 6000.

04:02.623 --> 04:04.825
UH-HUH.
 GREAT PLANE.

04:04.825 --> 04:06.917
YOU SHOULD CONSIDER
BUYING ONE,

04:06.917 --> 04:09.540
ASSUMING YOU DIDN'T LOSE
EVERYTHING IN YOUR DIVORCE.

04:09.540 --> 04:12.543
WELL, AS YOU CAN SEE,
I'VE BEEN ACQUIRING ASSETS.

04:12.543 --> 04:15.336
[ SIGHS ]
BY SACRIFICING SO MUCH.

04:15.336 --> 04:17.968
DO YOU MEAN THE HOUSE
OR VICTORIA?

04:17.968 --> 04:19.219
'CAUSE EITHER WAY,

04:19.219 --> 04:21.841
I'M HAPPY TO BE FREE
OF THAT FADING STRUCTURE.

04:21.841 --> 04:23.844
NOW THAT YOU'VE
HAD TIME TO CATCH UP,

04:23.844 --> 04:25.886
CAN WE GET DOWN
TO BUSINESS?

04:25.886 --> 04:28.689
ACTUALLY, WE'RE ON OUR WAY TO
THE CLUB FOR A ROUND OF TENNIS.

04:28.689 --> 04:30.230
YOUR FATHER'S
STILL SMARTING

04:30.230 --> 04:32.483
FROM THE TIME I BEAT HIM
IN SAINT TROPEZ.

04:32.483 --> 04:34.655
REVISIONIST HISTORY...
 [ CHUCKLES ]

04:34.655 --> 04:36.487
....A GRAYSON SPECIALITY.

04:36.487 --> 04:39.279
[ SPEAKS FRENCH ]

04:54.715 --> 04:57.918
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:57.918 --> 05:00.591
STEVIE. HI.

05:00.591 --> 05:02.302
IT'S BEEN AWHILE.

05:02.302 --> 05:05.636
HOW HAVE YOU BEEN
SINCE LAST WE MET?

05:05.636 --> 05:07.848
WELL,
I'M WORKING ON THINGS.

05:07.848 --> 05:10.140
ON MYSELF AND --
AND WITH DANIEL.

05:10.140 --> 05:12.893
WELL, THEN, I'M GLAD YOU WON'T
BE NEEDING MY SERVICES.

05:12.893 --> 05:16.196
ACTUALLY,
CAN WE TALK FOR A MOMENT?

05:17.778 --> 05:20.491
Jack: THOUGHT YOU MIGHT
WANT SOME OF THE GOOD STUFF

05:20.491 --> 05:22.112
BEFORE
WE HEAD OFF TO LUNCH.

05:22.112 --> 05:24.405
JACK, HI.

05:24.405 --> 05:27.247
YOU TWO
KNOW EACH OTHER?

05:27.247 --> 05:29.830
OH, EVERYBODY KNOWS EVERYBODY
AROUND HERE. [ CHUCKLES ]

05:29.830 --> 05:31.872
CAN -- CAN YOU EXCUSE US
FOR A SECOND?

05:31.872 --> 05:33.083
OF COURSE.

05:33.083 --> 05:34.795
EMILY, IT WAS GOOD
TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

05:34.795 --> 05:36.457
YES. YOU, TOO.

05:39.009 --> 05:41.221
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

05:41.221 --> 05:43.093
I JUST BUMPED
INTO STEVIE.

05:43.093 --> 05:45.516
RIGHT AFTER HER A.A. MEETING?
SEEMS AWFULLY CONVENIENT.

05:45.516 --> 05:47.428
WERE YOU HOPING
THAT I WOULDN'T BE HERE?

05:47.428 --> 05:48.849
LOOK, I JUST WANTED TO
ASK HER A FEW QUESTIONS.

05:48.849 --> 05:50.270
I KNOW THAT SHE'S A GRAYSON,
BUT SHE WAS GONE

05:50.270 --> 05:52.272
LONG BEFORE ALL THE STUFF
WITH YOUR FATHER HAPPENED.

05:52.272 --> 05:54.855
LOOK, YOU AND I ARE FINALLY
GETTING BACK TO A GOOD PLACE,

05:54.855 --> 05:57.027
AND I'M TRYING TO GET THERE
WITH MY MOM, TOO.

05:57.027 --> 06:01.532
PLEASE JUST LET ME
HAVE THIS ONE THING.

06:03.153 --> 06:05.746
LEAVE STEVIE OUT OF IT.

06:28.969 --> 06:30.180
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

06:33.514 --> 06:35.225
OH! HA HA!

06:35.225 --> 06:36.727
THAT IS MATCH!

06:36.727 --> 06:38.859
YOU'VE LOST YOUR TOUCH,
MY FRIEND.

06:38.859 --> 06:42.282
I'M SURPRISED YOU STILL
HAVE YOUR COMPETITIVE SPIRIT.

06:42.282 --> 06:46.196
I THOUGHT YOU WERE MORE
INTO FRIVOLOUS GAMES THESE DAYS.

06:46.196 --> 06:48.829
I ASSUME YOU'RE REFERRING
TO MY STEWARDSHIP OF VOULEZ.

06:48.829 --> 06:51.241
USING MY BRAND
TO PUBLISH YOUR MEMOIRS --

06:51.241 --> 06:53.664
IT'S BENEATH YOU.

06:53.664 --> 06:55.085
YEAH, WELL, I'VE DECIDED
TO PUT THOSE ON ICE.

06:55.085 --> 06:56.537
I MEAN, I'D HATE
FOR THE WORLD TO THINK

06:56.537 --> 06:58.038
THAT MY STORY'S
ANYWHERE NEAR OVER.

06:58.038 --> 07:00.420
NO,
I HAVE NEW ASPIRATIONS.

07:00.420 --> 07:02.422
AND WHAT ARE THEY?
THE FRENCH OPEN?

07:02.422 --> 07:03.804
WIMBLEDON?

07:03.804 --> 07:05.716
THAT'S ALWAYS BEEN
YOUR PROBLEM, PASCAL.

07:05.716 --> 07:07.718
YOU'RE TOO FIXATED
ON YOUR OWN CONTINENT.

07:07.718 --> 07:09.139
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:09.139 --> 07:13.053
AND WHERE
SHOULD I BE LOOKING?

07:13.053 --> 07:15.265
RIGHT HERE, THE AMERICAS,
WHERE I CAN SHEPHERD

07:15.265 --> 07:16.937
YOUR NEW NORTH AMERICAN
BASE OF OPERATIONS.

07:16.937 --> 07:20.020
I MEAN, THINK ABOUT IT --
A GRAYSON/LeMARCHAL ALLIANCE

07:20.020 --> 07:23.023
WOULD BE SOMETHING REMARKABLE
TO RECKON WITH.

07:23.023 --> 07:24.404
I REMEMBER
WHEN WE STARTED OUT,

07:24.404 --> 07:26.827
YOU SAID I WAS A FOOL
FOR RUNNING A MEDIA COMPANY.

07:26.827 --> 07:28.198
WELL, IT WAS
A FOOLISH THING TO SAY.

07:28.198 --> 07:30.991
NOW, INFORMATION
IS THE REAL SEAT OF POWER,

07:30.991 --> 07:32.993
AND VOULEZ IS JUST THE BASE
OF THE PYRAMID.

07:32.993 --> 07:35.626
CONSIDERING WHAT YOU'VE
ASKED OF ME IN THE PAST,

07:35.626 --> 07:38.579
I THINK I'VE DONE
ENOUGH FOR YOU.

07:40.000 --> 07:43.043
CONRAD. HMM, SHOWING UP
WHERE YOU DON'T BELONG.

07:43.043 --> 07:45.676
IF YOU REMEMBER, I GOT
THE MEMBERSHIP IN THE DIVORCE,

07:45.676 --> 07:47.678
HOPING TO
AVOID AWKWARD RUN-INS

07:47.678 --> 07:49.890
WHENEVER I CHOOSE
TO HAVE A QUIET LUNCH OUT.

07:49.890 --> 07:53.894
I WAS ON MY WAY OUT ANYWAY,
HAVING BESTED AN OLD FRIEND.

07:53.894 --> 07:57.477
HMM.
 VICTORIA,
YOU REMEMBER PASCAL.

08:00.981 --> 08:03.063
STILL LOSING TO CONRAD,
I SEE.

08:03.063 --> 08:05.696
JUST TRIED TO MAKE HIM
FEEL GOOD ABOUT HIMSELF --

08:05.696 --> 08:08.949
SOMETHING YOU FINALLY STOPPED
DOING AFTER 25 YEARS.

08:08.949 --> 08:11.872
DON'T FORGET -- YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO INTRODUCED US, PASCAL.

08:11.872 --> 08:14.955
I NEVER HAVE.

08:14.955 --> 08:17.958
BUT NOW THAT YOU'VE
GOT RID OF HIM,

08:17.958 --> 08:20.831
PERHAPS YOU'D LIKE
TO HAVE LUNCH WITH ME?

08:20.831 --> 08:23.794
OH, I'M SURE YOU'LL
FIGURE SOMETHING OUT.

08:23.794 --> 08:26.086
IF I REMEMBER CORRECTLY,

08:26.086 --> 08:28.589
YOU'RE NEVER ALONE
FOR VERY LONG.

08:37.267 --> 08:39.269
Margaux: OH-HOO.
 Jack: HEY, HEY, HEY.
LOOK WHO'S BACK.

08:39.269 --> 08:42.062
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT!

08:42.062 --> 08:46.026
I'M ONLY AWAY A SHORT TIME,
YET YOU'VE GROWN SO MUCH.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.408
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

08:48.408 --> 08:49.409
MM.

08:51.491 --> 08:53.493
HOW ARE THINGS
WITH THE HOUSE?

08:53.493 --> 08:56.577
WELL, ESCROW IS CLOSING
IN EIGHT DAYS, OR...

08:56.577 --> 08:58.118
HUIT JOURS.

08:58.118 --> 09:01.291
YOUR ACCENT IS...NOT BAD.
 NO?

09:01.291 --> 09:03.293
[ BOTH LAUGH ]
 ARE YOU LOOKING
TO IMPRESS MY FATHER?

09:03.293 --> 09:05.375
ACTUALLY, I WAS LOOKING
TO IMPRESS HIS DAUGHTER.

09:05.375 --> 09:08.008
YOUR FRENCH WILL BE PUT
TO BETTER USE WITH ME ANYWAY,

09:08.008 --> 09:10.841
BECAUSE I'M HOPING MY FATHER
WON'T STAY THROUGH TOMORROW.

09:10.841 --> 09:13.433
ALTHOUGH, THERE CONTINUE
TO BE RUMORS OF HIM

09:13.433 --> 09:15.515
GOING TO THE OPERA.

09:15.515 --> 09:17.517
[ CHUCKLES ]
 AND I GOT
YOUR MOTHER A TICKET.

09:17.517 --> 09:19.850
YOU --
 UNLESS YOU
THINK IT'S TOO SOON.

09:19.850 --> 09:21.021
NO.
 NO?

09:21.021 --> 09:23.183
NO, I W-- I WOULD LOVE
FOR YOU TO MEET HER.

09:23.183 --> 09:24.564
OKAY. FANTASTIC.

09:24.564 --> 09:26.276
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:29.319 --> 09:31.742
IS YOUR...

09:31.742 --> 09:33.784
YOUR FATHER
DRIVING YOU NUTS?

09:33.784 --> 09:36.957
I SIMPLY ASKED
FOR A LITTLE MUSCLE

09:36.957 --> 09:38.789
TO PUSH CONRAD OUT.

09:38.789 --> 09:41.581
WELL, INSTEAD,
HE FLIES HERE TO PLAY TENNIS,

09:41.581 --> 09:44.795
AND I'M BACK
TO BEING HIS LITTLE GIRL --

09:44.795 --> 09:47.087
OR AT LEAST
THAT'S HOW HE TREATS ME.

09:47.087 --> 09:48.588
RIGHT.

09:48.588 --> 09:51.712
WHEN I FIRST STARTED WORKING,
MY DAD, LIKE, WOULDN'T LET ME

09:51.712 --> 09:53.884
MAKE ANY OF THE DEPOSITS
OR DEAL WITH ANY OF THE VENDORS.

09:53.884 --> 09:56.977
WHAT DID YOU DO?

09:56.977 --> 09:58.348
WELL, I TOLD HIM TO GO TO HELL,
AND I DID IT ANYWAY.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

09:58.348 --> 09:59.810
AND IT WORKED OUT

09:59.810 --> 10:02.312
'CAUSE HE FINALLY STARTED
TRUSTING ME TO RUN THE BUSINESS.

10:02.312 --> 10:03.724
OF COURSE...

10:03.724 --> 10:06.526
WE RAN A BAR, NOT
A MULTIBILLION-DOLLAR COMPANY.

10:06.526 --> 10:08.028
A PARENT IS A PARENT.

10:08.028 --> 10:11.231
[ CARL BABBLES ]
 AND YOU'RE LUCKY
TO HAVE SUCH A GOOD ONE.

10:12.863 --> 10:14.444
MM-HMM.

10:20.000 --> 10:23.834
OH, YOU LOOK SUN-KISSED,
CONRAD.

10:23.834 --> 10:25.666
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:25.666 --> 10:28.749
I WAS BEATING AN OLD FRIEND
AT A GAME OF TENNIS --

10:28.749 --> 10:30.751
PASCAL LeMARCHAL.

10:30.751 --> 10:32.012
HMM.

10:32.012 --> 10:36.256
HE'D LIKE YOU --
SOPHISTICATED, SMART, BEAUTIFUL.

10:36.256 --> 10:39.890
AH, BUT ON THE DOWNSIDE,
YOU'RE HAPPILY MARRIED, RIGHT?

10:39.890 --> 10:44.895
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
ABOUT THAT...

10:44.895 --> 10:46.687
SO, YOU HAD ME
DRAG STEVIE BACK HERE

10:46.687 --> 10:49.439
JUST TO STIR UP TROUBLE
WITH VICTORIA?

10:49.439 --> 10:51.321
WELL, TO BE CLEAR,
I THOUGHT YOU WERE SINCERE

10:51.321 --> 10:52.983
ABOUT YOUR DESIRE
TO GET DIVORCED.

10:52.983 --> 10:55.986
BUT, YEAH, IT WAS A CONVENIENT
WAY TO GET BACK

10:55.986 --> 10:59.449
AT MY SECOND EX WHILE
MAKING AMENDS WITH MY FIRST.

10:59.449 --> 11:02.242
OH, WELL, FROM WHAT I HEAR,
YOU HAD NOTHING TO MAKE UP FOR.

11:02.242 --> 11:05.245
WASN'T STEVIE ON HER WAY
TO ROCK BOTTOM BACK IN THE DAY?

11:05.245 --> 11:07.878
WHILE WE WERE MARRIED,
YES.

11:07.878 --> 11:10.460
SO, DID SOMETHING HAPPEN
AFTER YOUR DIVORCE?

11:10.460 --> 11:13.053
WELL, WE CROSSED PATHS
A FEW YEARS LATER,

11:13.053 --> 11:16.256
AND SHE TRIED TO REINSERT
HERSELF INTO MY BUSINESS --

11:16.256 --> 11:19.139
NOT A GOOD CHOICE
FOR ANYONE.

11:19.139 --> 11:23.393
YOU KNOW, IN THE LONG RUN,
I PROBABLY DID HER A FAVOR.

11:23.393 --> 11:25.976
STILL...

11:31.441 --> 11:33.233
[ FUSSING ]

11:33.233 --> 11:37.657
THERE YOU GO.
HERE'S YOUR BLANKET, SWEET BOY.

11:37.657 --> 11:38.779
SO, THIS MARGAUX --

11:38.779 --> 11:40.620
WHEN DO
I GET TO MEET HER?

11:40.620 --> 11:42.913
[ CHUCKLES ]
HOW ABOUT TOMORROW NIGHT?

11:42.913 --> 11:45.125
THIS MUST BE LOVE
IF YOU'RE GOING TO THE OPERA.

11:45.125 --> 11:47.127
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]
 I'M IN.

11:47.127 --> 11:48.628
YEAH, SHE, UH...

11:48.628 --> 11:50.791
SHE KIND OF TOOK ME
BY SURPRISE.

11:54.885 --> 11:56.887
I'M PROUD OF YOU,
JACK.

11:58.759 --> 12:01.391
MOVING ON
IS A BRAVE THING.

12:03.804 --> 12:06.807
THOUGH I SEE THIS,
AND...

12:06.807 --> 12:09.189
[ SIGHS ]
...I WISH I'D HAD THE COURAGE

12:09.189 --> 12:10.941
TO GET BACK
IN YOUR LIFE SOONER --

12:10.941 --> 12:15.315
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE
I COULD HAVE MET HER,

12:15.315 --> 12:19.529
BUT...
[ SIGHS ]

12:19.529 --> 12:22.122
WHAT?

12:22.122 --> 12:24.704
IT'S SILLY.

12:24.704 --> 12:27.747
MAYBE THINGS WOULD HAVE
TURNED OUT DIFFERENT.

12:31.872 --> 12:33.874
TRUST ME.

12:33.874 --> 12:37.297
WHAT HAPPENED
WAS GONNA HAPPEN.

12:40.841 --> 12:43.433
I MET AMANDA'S FATHER
ONCE IN PRISON.

12:44.975 --> 12:47.978
I WAS ONE OF THE PEOPLE
THAT THOUGHT HE GOT A RAW DEAL.

12:47.978 --> 12:49.389
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

12:49.389 --> 12:51.101
AND IF YOU DON'T
MIND ME ASKING,

12:51.101 --> 12:54.064
WHAT DID AMANDA
BELIEVE?

12:56.316 --> 12:59.900
THAT HER FATHER
WAS AN INNOCENT MAN.

12:59.900 --> 13:02.112
AND YOU?

13:02.112 --> 13:04.905
THAT THE PEOPLE
WHO FOLLOW THIS PATH

13:04.905 --> 13:08.708
END UP HURT...OR WORSE.

13:08.708 --> 13:12.412
BECAUSE OF MY FORMER HUSBAND
AND HIS FAMILY?

13:12.412 --> 13:13.793
YES.

13:13.793 --> 13:15.836
WHICH IS WHY
I'D LIKE TO DROP IT.

13:18.468 --> 13:20.881
[ SIGHS ]

13:32.432 --> 13:34.895
MARTA.

13:34.895 --> 13:38.278
YOU'RE REQUESTED
IN THE STUDY, MRS. GRAYSON.

13:43.073 --> 13:46.496
WELL, I'M GLAD TO SEE YOU
FINALLY CAME TO YOUR SENSES

13:46.496 --> 13:48.078
AND HIRED
THE STAFF BACK.

13:48.078 --> 13:50.951
WELL, NOW THAT YOU'RE LEAVING,
I FIGURED IT WAS TIME.

13:50.951 --> 13:52.873
EXCUSE ME?

14:00.630 --> 14:04.224
WE'RE GETTING A DIVORCE.

14:04.224 --> 14:06.426
AS A SIGN OF GOOD FAITH,
I'VE ACCESSED FAMILY FUNDS

14:06.426 --> 14:09.059
TO MAKE YOU AN OFFER THAT
SHOULD LAST SEVERAL DECADES,

14:09.059 --> 14:11.851
SINCE I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU COVET OUR LIFESTYLE.

14:11.851 --> 14:13.733
IT'S FAR MORE
THAN YOU DESERVE,

14:13.733 --> 14:15.936
BUT SMALL PRICE TO PAY
TO GET YOU OUT.

14:15.936 --> 14:19.319
YES, BUT ACCORDING TO THE LEGAL
DEFINITION OF ADULTERY,

14:19.319 --> 14:20.740
THIS DOESN'T
PROVE A THING.

14:20.740 --> 14:25.115
WELL, WE'LL SEE ABOUT THAT
WHEN WE HAUL YOU INTO COURT.

14:25.115 --> 14:27.697
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

14:29.579 --> 14:31.791
I FORGAVE DANIEL
FOR SO MUCH.

14:31.791 --> 14:34.124
HE SHOT ME ON THE NIGHT

14:34.124 --> 14:36.917
THAT SHOULD HAVE BEEN
A DREAM COME TRUE

14:36.917 --> 14:39.379
AND FORCED ME
INTO BLAMING LYDIA DAVIS.

14:39.379 --> 14:42.632
I DID IT ALL
FOR DANIEL.

14:42.632 --> 14:46.346
AFTER EVERYTHING WE'VE BEEN
THROUGH, ALL OF THE ANGUISH,

14:46.346 --> 14:48.138
WHO COULD BLAME ME
FOR FINDING COMFORT

14:48.138 --> 14:49.849
IN THE ARMS
OF SOMEONE ELSE?

14:51.891 --> 14:53.723
[ SIGHS ]

14:53.723 --> 14:56.606
CONSIDER THAT A PREVIEW
TO MY TESTIMONY.

14:56.606 --> 14:58.648
I'LL SEE YOU AT THE OPERA
TOMORROW, DANIEL.

14:58.648 --> 15:00.020
YOU, TOO, VICTORIA.

15:00.020 --> 15:02.362
LET HER GO.

15:03.783 --> 15:05.825
SHE'S TRYING TO
GOAD YOU.

15:05.825 --> 15:07.657
I WANT HER OUT.

15:12.412 --> 15:14.204
BUT I THOUGHT
YOU WANTED A DIVORCE.

15:14.204 --> 15:16.456
OH, I'LL GET ONE
WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT.

15:16.456 --> 15:18.628
WELL, SOUNDS LIKE YOU
HANDLED IT WITH PANACHE.

15:18.628 --> 15:19.709
STILL,
I CAN'T BELIEVE DANIEL

15:19.709 --> 15:21.751
HAD A TAIL ON ME
AND I DIDN'T KNOW IT.

15:21.751 --> 15:24.344
WELL, YOU WERE A LITTLE
OFF YOUR GAME AT THE TIME.

15:24.344 --> 15:26.756
WELL, NOW THAT I'M BACK,
THE LAST THING I NEED IS
DANIEL TRACKING MY EVERY MOVE.

15:26.756 --> 15:28.638
I CAN'T AFFORD
ANY MORE WILD CARDS.

15:28.638 --> 15:30.510
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

15:36.396 --> 15:38.148
EMILY GRAYSON.

15:38.148 --> 15:41.901
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHO YOU REALLY ARE?

15:50.950 --> 15:53.033
"EVERYBODY KNOWS EVERYBODY" --
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID, RIGHT?

15:53.033 --> 15:54.995
BUT WAS EVERYBODY
THE MAID OF HONOR

15:54.995 --> 15:57.077
AT AMANDA'S WEDDING?

15:57.077 --> 15:59.129
[ SCOFFS ]

15:59.129 --> 16:03.713
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN QUITE
THE BETRAYAL TO THE GRAYSONS --

16:03.713 --> 16:05.545
YOU SUPPORTING
A CLARKE --

16:05.545 --> 16:09.179
UNLESS YOU WERE
DOUBLE-CROSSING AMANDA.

16:09.179 --> 16:11.091
DOES JACK
SUSPECT SOMETHING?

16:12.642 --> 16:14.224
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW
WHO YOU THINK I AM,

16:14.224 --> 16:16.596
BUT I'M NOT JUST ANOTHER WITNESS
THAT YOU CAN TOY WITH.

16:16.596 --> 16:20.560
YOU CALL ME INTO TOWN UNDER
THE GUISE OF HATING DANIEL,

16:20.560 --> 16:22.062
AND THEN YOU CLAIM
TO BE HAPPY.

16:22.062 --> 16:23.563
I THINK IT'S PRETTY CLEAR

16:23.563 --> 16:27.197
THAT YOU HAVEN'T BEEN HONEST
WITH ME SINCE THE MOMENT WE MET.

16:27.197 --> 16:30.780
WHY SHOULD I
BELIEVE YOU'RE AN ALLY?

16:32.412 --> 16:35.995
BECAUSE AMANDA
WAS LIKE A SISTER TO ME.

16:35.995 --> 16:39.289
AND WHAT THE GRAYSONS DID TO HER
AND HER FATHER MAKES ME SICK.

16:39.289 --> 16:42.922
SO...

16:42.922 --> 16:45.465
THE REAL THE QUESTION IS,
WHY ARE YOU MARRIED TO DANIEL?

16:47.927 --> 16:49.509
WHAT'S YOUR STAKE
IN THIS?

16:49.509 --> 16:51.131
LIKE AMANDA...

16:54.094 --> 16:57.137
...MAYBE YOU...

16:57.137 --> 17:00.140
I THINK DAVID CLARKE
WAS INNOCENT.

17:06.406 --> 17:08.608
DID YOU EVER
DO ANYTHING ABOUT IT?

17:08.608 --> 17:10.819
I TRIED.

17:10.819 --> 17:12.952
I EVEN
MET WITH HIM ONCE.

17:14.654 --> 17:16.455
A FEW DAYS LATER,

17:16.455 --> 17:22.462
I WAS PULLED OVER
AND BLEW A 0.14.

17:22.462 --> 17:26.876
I NEVER DROVE DRUNK.
CONRAD HAD SET ME UP.

17:26.876 --> 17:31.050
AND A D.U.I. IS GROUNDS
FOR DISBARMENT.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.632
AND IF HE WAS WILLING
TO GO THAT FAR,

17:32.632 --> 17:34.514
AT LEAST YOU KNOW
YOU WERE ONTO SOMETHING.

17:34.514 --> 17:37.097
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR ANSWERS,
TOO, AREN'T YOU?

17:37.097 --> 17:39.018
FOR AMANDA.

17:41.101 --> 17:43.233
MAYBE I CAN HELP.

17:43.233 --> 17:47.026
[ SIGHS ]

17:47.026 --> 17:49.399
THANKS, STEVIE, BUT...
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

17:49.399 --> 17:51.030
...AFTER EVERYTHING
THAT'S HAPPENED,

17:51.030 --> 17:54.073
IT'S IMPORTANT FOR ME
TO PUT JACK'S FEELINGS FIRST.

17:54.073 --> 17:55.865
AND...

17:55.865 --> 17:57.957
I KNOW
HE WANTS TO LET THIS GO.

18:03.042 --> 18:06.666
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

18:06.666 --> 18:09.259
[ LOCK TURNS ]

18:09.259 --> 18:12.842
[ CLATTER IN DISTANCE ]

18:17.717 --> 18:19.599
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

18:23.183 --> 18:26.396
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
JAVIER?

18:27.777 --> 18:29.819
SOMEBODY DIDN'T FORGET
WHAT I TAUGHT HIM INSIDE.

18:29.819 --> 18:31.991
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

18:31.991 --> 18:34.033
[ Chuckling ] I WAS LOOKING
FOR A BOTTLE OPENER.

18:34.033 --> 18:35.405
[ SIGHS ]

18:35.405 --> 18:39.038
PLEASE TELL ME YOU DID NOT
HACK YOUR WAY OUT OF PRISON.

18:39.038 --> 18:42.242
NO, MAN. I'M OUT.
ON THE UP-AND-UP.

18:42.242 --> 18:44.043
[ SCOFFS ]

18:44.043 --> 18:45.665
AND BREAKING
THE LAW ALREADY.

18:45.665 --> 18:47.917
YOU HAVE SOME SERIOUS
SECURITY BREACHES,

18:47.917 --> 18:49.419
WHICH I CAN
HELP YOU WITH.

18:49.419 --> 18:50.630
[ SIGHS ]

18:50.630 --> 18:51.711
YOU SAID I COULD
CRASH HERE.

18:51.711 --> 18:53.843
I-IF YOU HAD
NOWHERE ELSE TO ST--

18:55.014 --> 18:57.557
YOU HAVE NOWHERE ELSE
TO STAY.

18:58.598 --> 19:00.600
BUT WHAT ABOUT YOUR MOM?

19:00.600 --> 19:01.971
YOU'D THINK SHE'D APPRECIATE
THAT I USED THE MONEY I STOLE

19:01.971 --> 19:03.813
FROM THE N.S.A. TO PUT HER
THROUGH NIGHT SCHOOL,

19:03.813 --> 19:05.815
BUT SHE JUST CAN'T SEEM TO
GET OVER THE FIRST PART

19:05.815 --> 19:08.147
OR THE "GETTING CAUGHT"
PART.

19:08.147 --> 19:09.939
[ CHUCKLES ] WELL,
YOU WERE KIND OF AN IDIOT.

19:09.939 --> 19:12.362
I MEAN, SIGNING YOUR HACKS
WITH AN ANAGRAM OF YOUR NAME?

19:12.362 --> 19:14.574
WHICH YOU TOLD ME,
LIKE, EVERY DAY.

19:14.574 --> 19:17.156
YEAH, BECAUSE YOU
HAD A LOT TO LEARN,

19:17.156 --> 19:20.870
AND I HAD A LOT OF TIME
TO TEACH YOU.

19:20.870 --> 19:22.832
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ME
PUT IT TO GOOD USE, HUH?

19:22.832 --> 19:24.834
COME ON. WHAT DO YOU GOT
IN THE HOPPER THESE DAYS?

19:24.834 --> 19:26.836
I BET IT
IS SOMETHING HUGE.

19:26.836 --> 19:28.248
ALL RIGHT,
YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:28.248 --> 19:30.089
DON'T WORRY ABOUT
WHAT I'M WORKING ON.

19:30.089 --> 19:33.883
JUST...FOCUS ON FINDING
YOURSELF A PLACE TO STAY.

19:33.883 --> 19:37.797
FOR NOW...
I CAN CRASH?

19:37.797 --> 19:39.969
[ SIGHS ]

19:39.969 --> 19:44.514
FOR ONE DAY.
ONE DAY ONLY.

19:49.689 --> 19:51.651
I HAD TO MEET THE MAN

19:51.651 --> 19:54.444
WHO TOOK SNAPSHOTS
OF THE WILIEST PERSON I KNOW.

19:54.444 --> 19:55.485
YOU'RE GOOD.

19:55.485 --> 19:58.077
THANK YOU,
MRS. GRAYSON.

19:58.077 --> 20:01.160
BUT YOUR SON SAID I'D SATISFIED
HIS NEED FOR MY SERVICES.

20:01.160 --> 20:04.163
WELL, I HAVE A NEW ANGLE
I'M WORKING ON,

20:04.163 --> 20:06.826
AND I THINK YOU'RE
JUST THE PERSON TO HELP ME OUT.

20:06.826 --> 20:08.248
[ DOORS OPEN ]

20:08.248 --> 20:10.129
EXCUSE ME, MRS. GRAYSON,
BUT YOUR DRESS HAS ARRIVED.

20:10.129 --> 20:11.711
ALREADY?

20:11.711 --> 20:14.544
OH.
WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME?

20:21.010 --> 20:22.472
PASCAL.

20:22.472 --> 20:24.684
I HAD AN INSPIRATION FOR WHAT
YOU COULD WEAR TO THE OPERA.

20:24.684 --> 20:26.396
WELL, I APPLAUD
YOUR PRESUMPTION.

20:26.396 --> 20:28.017
I'VE ALREADY
PICKED OUT A GOWN.

20:28.017 --> 20:29.769
NOT LIKE THIS ONE.

20:29.769 --> 20:33.022
I HAD IT OVERNIGHTED
BY THE DESIGNERS.

20:33.022 --> 20:35.275
YOUR FRIENDS
WITH DOLCE & GABBANA?

20:35.275 --> 20:37.357
I HAVE MANY FRIENDS.

20:37.357 --> 20:39.949
WELL, I RECENTLY HAD DINNER
WITH DOMENICO.

20:39.949 --> 20:41.741
YOUR NAME
DIDN'T COME UP.

20:41.741 --> 20:43.663
OH, REALLY?
 MM-HMM.

20:43.663 --> 20:47.787
WELL, I'M TRYING NOT TO GIVE
PEOPLE REASONS TO TALK ABOUT ME.

20:47.787 --> 20:50.290
WHICH IS A BIG DIFFERENCE
FROM THE MAN I MET YEARS AGO.

20:50.290 --> 20:53.873
[ SCOFFS ]
I HAVE CHANGED.

20:53.873 --> 20:57.677
SO HAVE YOU.
DIVORCE SUITS YOU.

20:57.677 --> 21:00.680
YOUR CHARMS WON'T
WORK ON ME, PASCAL.

21:00.680 --> 21:02.382
NOT THIS TIME.

21:03.763 --> 21:07.387
PERHAPS WE SHOULD GO,
THEN.

21:07.387 --> 21:09.979
OH, MAYBE I SHOULD
TRY ON THAT GOWN.

21:11.651 --> 21:13.813
THE DESIGNERS ARE FRIENDS
OF MINE, AFTER ALL.

21:13.813 --> 21:16.195
I WOULDN'T
WANT TO OFFEND.

21:16.195 --> 21:17.657
AND IT'S STUNNING.

21:17.657 --> 21:20.660
I LOOK FORWARD TO SEEING YOU
AT "PAGLIACCI."

21:22.612 --> 21:24.614
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

21:26.616 --> 21:28.998
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

21:28.998 --> 21:32.001
SAW EMILY LAST NIGHT.

21:32.001 --> 21:35.415
DID SHE CALL YOU?

21:35.415 --> 21:37.086
I WENT TO HER.

21:37.086 --> 21:39.679
HMM.
 WHAT'S GOING ON THERE?

21:39.679 --> 21:40.800
[ Chuckling ] NOTHING.

21:40.800 --> 21:44.263
SHE SENT ME AWAY
OUT OF LOYALTY TO YOU.

21:44.263 --> 21:47.477
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH
A LOT.

21:47.477 --> 21:50.850
AND THE LAWYER IN ME SAYS YOU
BOTH WANT TO DO RIGHT BY AMANDA,

21:50.850 --> 21:52.932
SO WHY DISCOURAGE THAT?

21:58.277 --> 22:02.071
I KNOW IT'S SELFISH,
BUT...

22:02.071 --> 22:05.535
I DON'T WANT ANOTHER THING
TAKEN FROM ME.

22:05.535 --> 22:08.287
THIS IS
WORTH FIGHTING FOR.

22:08.287 --> 22:10.620
I DON'T KNOW
THAT IT IS.

22:10.620 --> 22:13.623
AN INNOCENT MAN
WAS PUT BEHIND BARS.

22:13.623 --> 22:16.626
IF THERE'S ANYTHING THAT
CAN BE DONE, I WANT TO HELP.

22:18.087 --> 22:20.880
IT'S THAT IMPORTANT
TO YOU?

22:20.880 --> 22:24.964
CASES LIKE DAVID CLARKE'S WERE
THE REASON I BECAME A LAWYER.

22:24.964 --> 22:28.097
I WANTED TO BE IN THE TRENCHES,
FIGHTING FOR THE UNDERDOG,

22:28.097 --> 22:31.521
WHICH IS WHAT I DO EVERY DAY
IN MY DIVORCE PRACTICE.

22:31.521 --> 22:35.064
FOR ME,
IT'S ALL ABOUT JUSTICE.

22:35.064 --> 22:38.858
AND HOW WERE YOU GONNA
GET THAT FOR DAVID CLARKE?

22:42.692 --> 22:46.325
AFTER HE WAS CONVICTED,
I LOOKED INTO HIS CASE,

22:46.325 --> 22:48.908
AND I RECEIVED
A SUSPICIOUS PIECE OF EVIDENCE,

22:48.908 --> 22:52.792
BUT I COULDN'T
VERIFY THE SOURCE.

22:52.792 --> 22:57.206
ONCE I WAS DISBARRED,
MY FIRM CONFISCATED EVERYTHING.

22:57.206 --> 23:02.301
AND WITH THAT...
WENT ALL HOPE.

23:02.301 --> 23:05.505
NOW THERE'S NO WAY
TO GET THAT INFORMATION.

23:05.505 --> 23:08.718
[ TAPS COUNTER ]

23:08.718 --> 23:11.891
Nolan:
PUSH THE 36th FLOOR.

23:11.891 --> 23:13.893
[ SIGHS ]
 JACK, YOU SURE
YOU'RE UP FOR THIS?

23:13.893 --> 23:15.605
WELL, IF YOU COULD HAVE
JUST HACKED THE FILES, THEN --

23:15.605 --> 23:17.567
WELL, IF YOU'D WANTED SOMETHING
FROM THIS CENTURY, NO PROBLEM,

23:17.567 --> 23:20.359
BUT EVERYTHING ELSE IS
ON HARD DRIVES THAT AREN'T
CONNECTED TO ANYTHING ELSE.

23:20.359 --> 23:23.322
SO, THEREFORE, YOU
HAVE TO PHYSICALLY
BREAK INTO THEIR ARCHIVES.

23:23.322 --> 23:25.284
AND THIS THING'S RIGGED
TO OPEN THE SECURITY DOOR?

23:25.284 --> 23:27.026
HMM. IT WILL BE.

23:27.026 --> 23:28.528
[ CHUCKLES ]
LOOK, ONCE YOU'RE IN,

23:28.528 --> 23:30.830
YOU'RE GONNA LOCATE
THE JUNE 1997 HARD --

23:30.830 --> 23:32.622
GRAB IT AND GET OUT OF THERE.
I KNOW. YEAH.

23:32.622 --> 23:35.294
I WILL MEET YOU
AFTER MY MEETING.

23:35.294 --> 23:39.298
MS. STEVIE'S OLD FIRM
IS FAIRLY HIGH-PROFILE,

23:39.298 --> 23:40.630
AND I NEED NEW LAWYERS

23:40.630 --> 23:42.502
IF I'M GONNA FLOOD THE MARKET
WITH NEW PRODUCT.

23:42.502 --> 23:46.546
JACK, I CAN'T KEEP DEPRIVING
THE WORLD OF MY GENIUS.

23:46.546 --> 23:47.887
YEAH, ABOUT THAT, DO YOU WANT ME
TO STOP THE ELEVATOR?

23:47.887 --> 23:50.510
I JUST HAVE TO GET
THROUGH THE SECURITY FIREWALL

23:50.510 --> 23:54.013
THROUGH THE NETWORK, AND THEN
WE SHOULD BE GOOD TO GO.

23:54.013 --> 23:56.606
ALMOST THERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:56.606 --> 23:58.147
[ BEEPING ]
 OH, JACK OF LITTLE FAITH.

23:58.147 --> 24:00.019
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

24:03.483 --> 24:06.486
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:09.118 --> 24:10.910
THIS JUST CAME FOR YOU.
 THANK YOU.

24:10.910 --> 24:12.492
NOLAN ROSS.

24:12.492 --> 24:14.453
I HAVE A MEETING WITH THE HEAD
OF THE PATENT DEPARTMENT.

24:14.453 --> 24:17.497
YES, MR. ROSS.
ONE SECOND, PLEASE.

24:17.497 --> 24:19.078
NOLAN ROSS
IS HERE TO SEE YOU, SIR.

24:19.078 --> 24:21.501
PLEASE HAVE A SEAT.
HE'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

24:21.501 --> 24:23.042
THANKS.

24:26.085 --> 24:28.087
[ BEEPING, LOCK CLICKS ]

24:35.515 --> 24:38.518
JUNE '97.

24:38.518 --> 24:41.480
JUNE '97.

24:41.480 --> 24:44.483
[ SIGHS ]

24:44.483 --> 24:46.405
THERE AIN'T NO DATES.

24:54.453 --> 24:56.616
LOOK, I WORK FAST, SO I WANT
A TEAM THAT CAN SECURE PATENTS

24:56.616 --> 24:59.669
AS QUICKLY
AS I'M GOING TO NEED THEM.

24:59.669 --> 25:02.622
ALL DUE RESPECT,
MR. ROSS, SEEMS OF LATE,

25:02.622 --> 25:06.586
YOUR LEGAL NEEDS ARE MORE THE
"KEEP ME OFF DEATH ROW" KIND.

25:08.177 --> 25:13.553
WELL, LAST YEAR WAS FRAUGHT
WITH UNFORESEEABLE OBSTACLES,

25:13.553 --> 25:16.475
BUT I AM READY
TO CHART A NEW COURSE.

25:16.475 --> 25:17.687
WELL,
IF THAT'S THE CASE,

25:17.687 --> 25:20.019
WE MAY BE INTERESTED
IN YOUR COMEBACK.

25:20.019 --> 25:21.561
DON'T CALL IT A COMEBACK.

25:21.561 --> 25:23.603
I'VE BEEN HERE FOR YEARS.
 [ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

25:26.566 --> 25:28.698
EXCUSE ME.

25:28.698 --> 25:30.529
OUR TIME IS MONEY,
MR. ROSS.

25:30.529 --> 25:33.412
AND I CAN AFFORD IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:36.746 --> 25:38.247
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

25:39.619 --> 25:40.750
[ BEEP ]
 NOLAN!

25:40.750 --> 25:42.251
JAVIER: Nope.
You got upgraded to Javier.

25:42.251 --> 25:44.624
DO YOU KNOW WHAT YEAR THE FIRM
WAS FOUNDED?

25:44.624 --> 25:46.626
I'M SORRY. WHO IS THIS?
 DO YOU WANT
THEIR INFO OR MINE?

25:46.626 --> 25:49.338
WHAT YEAR, AND WHAT'S
THE FIRST NUMBER ON THE DRIVES?

25:51.470 --> 25:53.472
ALL RIGHT. UH...

25:53.472 --> 25:55.304
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

25:55.304 --> 25:59.478
UH, UH, 1978,
AND, UM, E23754.

25:59.478 --> 26:01.270
ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S NOT "56"?

26:01.270 --> 26:03.603
YOU'RE RIGHT. IT'S 56.
 Thought so.

26:03.603 --> 26:05.234
IT'S A BASIC
ROLLING-CODE CRYPTO.

26:05.234 --> 26:07.647
I SAW TATS IN PRISON THAT WERE
HARDER TO FIGURE OUT THAN THAT.

26:07.647 --> 26:09.949
OH, RIGHT. OF COURSE.

26:09.949 --> 26:11.570
You're Nolan's friend
from prison.

26:11.570 --> 26:13.032
OKAY,
YOU WANT JUNE '97.

26:13.032 --> 26:15.034
It's gonna be L39935,
L39936.

26:15.034 --> 26:18.197
AND GRAB L39937
IN CASE YOU READ WRONG AGAIN.

26:18.197 --> 26:19.619
And I just broke my probation
on landline,

26:19.619 --> 26:24.293
WHICH IS GONNA BE TRACED
IN 5, 4, 3 -- LATER.

26:24.293 --> 26:27.086
[ BEEP ]

26:27.086 --> 26:29.008
L39935.

26:29.008 --> 26:32.591
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:32.591 --> 26:35.214
YOU'RE STILL HERE.

26:35.214 --> 26:37.807
I THOUGHT WITHOUT A FUTURE
AS A PARTNER,

26:37.807 --> 26:39.639
YOU WOULD LOSE INTEREST
IN VOULEZ.

26:39.639 --> 26:43.062
I WAS CURIOUS AS TO HOW,
IN THIS NEW-MEDIA ERA,

26:43.062 --> 26:45.604
A MAGAZINE COULD
START OUT SO SUCCESSFULLY,

26:45.604 --> 26:48.437
SO I HAD A FORENSIC ACCOUNTANT
LOOK INTO THE BOOKS,

26:48.437 --> 26:52.692
AND I-I THINK I MAY HAVE
UNDERESTIMATED YOU, PASCAL.

26:52.692 --> 26:55.494
YOU ALSO UNDERESTIMATE THE POWER
OF THE LEMARCHAL NAME.

26:55.494 --> 26:57.326
Margaux: HE'S RIGHT.

26:57.326 --> 26:59.699
NOW GET OUT.

26:59.699 --> 27:01.330
THAT'S MY GIRL.

27:01.330 --> 27:03.162
NO, I'M TALKING TO YOU,
PASCAL.

27:05.124 --> 27:08.377
THIS IS MY MAGAZINE.
ITS SUCCESS IS BECAUSE OF ME.

27:08.377 --> 27:10.670
BUT YOUR PRESENCE HERE
IS NOT ONLY UNNEEDED,

27:10.670 --> 27:12.922
IT'S UNWANTED.

27:12.922 --> 27:14.513
[ SCOFFS ]

27:14.513 --> 27:17.466
SEE? THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOU HAVE KIDS TOO YOUNG.

27:17.466 --> 27:19.138
YOU DON'T
RAISE THEM PROPERLY.

27:19.138 --> 27:21.220
OH, WELL, THAT MAY BE SO,

27:21.220 --> 27:22.391
BUT ALLOW ME
TO APPLAUD YOUR SUCCESS

27:22.391 --> 27:24.473
AT RAISING
THE BOTTOM LINE.

27:24.473 --> 27:28.858
IT APPEARS, MARGAUX,
THAT VOULEZ IS LOSING MONEY

27:28.858 --> 27:32.271
TO THE TUNE
OF A MILLION EVERY QUARTER.

27:32.271 --> 27:34.363
OUR LEDGERS SHOW
WE'RE IN THE BLACK, CONRAD.

27:34.363 --> 27:35.695
NO, THAT'S TRUE.

27:35.695 --> 27:37.987
BUT WHEN THEY CROSS THE POND
TO PASCAL'S ACCOUNTANTS,

27:37.987 --> 27:39.779
THE NUMBERS CHANGE.

27:39.779 --> 27:42.371
THAT'S A SAVVY MOVE, PASCAL --
INDULGING YOUR DAUGHTER

27:42.371 --> 27:44.493
WHILE CREATING
A HANDSOME QUARTERLY WRITE-OFF.

27:46.165 --> 27:47.787
WHAT? IS THIS TRUE?

27:49.879 --> 27:52.882
THIS IS WHY I SAID BUSINESS
WASN'T FOR YOU, SWEETHEART.

27:52.882 --> 27:55.094
YOU'RE AN EVIL MAN.

27:55.094 --> 27:59.138
NOW THIS FROM A WOMAN WHO FIRED
MY SON TO SAVE HER COMPANY,

27:59.138 --> 28:00.469
WHOM YOU'RE MORE THAN WELCOME
TO REINSTATE ONCE I'VE MOVED

28:00.469 --> 28:04.513
INTO THE LeMARCHAL
MANHATTAN HEADQUARTERS.

28:04.513 --> 28:07.266
THAT'S ASSUMING WE NOW
SEE EYE-TO-EYE, PASCAL.

28:07.266 --> 28:11.270
ARE YOU SURE YOU WANT TO
GO DOWN THAT ROAD?

28:11.270 --> 28:12.651
HMM?

28:14.483 --> 28:17.486
'CAUSE
IT GOES BACK 20 YEARS.

28:25.414 --> 28:29.418
IT WAS IMPORTANT TO STEVIE
THAT YOU HAVE THEM.

28:29.418 --> 28:30.669
WHY DID YOU DO THIS?

28:30.669 --> 28:32.251
BECAUSE YOUR FATHER
WAS IMPORTANT TO ME, TOO.

28:32.251 --> 28:34.093
I DON'T WANT YOU
INVOLVED, JACK.

28:34.093 --> 28:36.255
EMILY, YOUR DAD WAS A GOOD MAN,
AN INNOCENT MAN.

28:36.255 --> 28:38.297
AND ISN'T THAT WHAT THIS
IS ALL ABOUT?

28:38.297 --> 28:41.470
THE FIGHT FOR JUSTICE?
 THIS IS MY FIGHT,
NOT YOURS.

28:41.470 --> 28:43.512
WOULD YOU
JUST LET ME HELP?
 NO!

28:43.512 --> 28:46.936
[ SIGHS ]
LOOK, YOU WERE RIGHT.

28:46.936 --> 28:48.397
WE'RE FINALLY GETTING
BACK TO A GOOD PLACE.

28:48.397 --> 28:51.690
I HONORED
WHAT YOU ASKED ME BEFORE --

28:51.690 --> 28:54.313
I LEFT
YOUR MOTHER ALONE.

28:54.313 --> 28:56.485
I NEED YOU
TO DO THE SAME.

28:56.485 --> 28:58.697
JUST STAY OUT OF IT.
PLEASE.

29:10.419 --> 29:12.211
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

29:12.211 --> 29:13.422
I RETAINED YOUR P.I.,

29:13.422 --> 29:15.464
WHO DISCOVERED
THAT AIDEN'S IN BERMUDA,

29:15.464 --> 29:18.677
WHICH IS GOOD BECAUSE IT MEANS
HE POSES NO IMMINENT THREAT.

29:18.677 --> 29:21.300
HOLD ON A SECOND,
Y-YOU'RE USING MY DETECTIVE?

29:21.300 --> 29:23.092
SINCE WHEN?

29:23.092 --> 29:26.685
SINCE EMILY REJECTED
THAT HUGE SETTLEMENT.

29:26.685 --> 29:28.477
I WAS TESTING HER, DANIEL.

29:28.477 --> 29:31.730
GRIFTERS HAVE THEIR PRICE,
AND EMILY COULDN'T BE BOUGHT.

29:31.730 --> 29:34.273
SHE'S TARGETING OUR FAMILY
AND NOT OUR FORTUNE.

29:34.273 --> 29:36.195
THE BEST WAY
TO EXPOSE WHAT SHE'S AFTER

29:36.195 --> 29:37.897
IS TO KEEP HER
HERE WITH YOU.

29:37.897 --> 29:41.320
[ CHUCKLES ] ABSOLUTELY NOT.
I'M GETTING THAT DIVORCE.

29:41.320 --> 29:46.285
DON'T YOU FIND IT ODD THAT SHE
HAPPENED TO DATE AIDEN MATHIS,

29:46.285 --> 29:49.208
WHOSE FATHER PLANTED THE BOMB
ON FLIGHT 197

29:49.208 --> 29:51.040
AND THAT SHE WAS CLOSE
WITH AMANDA CLARKE,

29:51.040 --> 29:53.462
WHOSE CHILDHOOD HOME
SHE WAS LIVING IN.

29:53.462 --> 29:56.295
THERE'S A CONNECTION.

29:56.295 --> 29:58.337
I'M GOING TO
FIND OUT WHAT HER PLAN IS.

29:58.337 --> 29:59.758
TO WHAT END?

29:59.758 --> 30:03.342
YOUR THEORIES COULD TAKE MONTHS
OR EVEN YEARS TO PROVE.

30:03.342 --> 30:05.925
NOW, RIGHT NOW THE ONLY PLAN
THAT I'M CONCERNED ABOUT

30:05.925 --> 30:07.186
IS GETTING HER THE HELL
OUT OF MY LIFE.

30:11.350 --> 30:13.482
[ DOOR OPENS ]

30:13.482 --> 30:15.694
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

30:15.694 --> 30:17.857
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

30:17.857 --> 30:20.279
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

30:20.279 --> 30:21.650
[ SIGHS ]

30:21.650 --> 30:23.442
I SHOULD HAVE
TOLD YOU JACK APPROACHED ME.

30:23.442 --> 30:25.784
WELL, IT CAN'T HAPPEN
AGAIN, NOLAN.

30:25.784 --> 30:27.366
WE'VE TALKED ABOUT THIS.
WHAT THE --

30:27.366 --> 30:29.578
WHERE THE HELL DID YOU EVEN
GET THIS STUFF?

30:29.578 --> 30:34.123
[ SIGHS ] JAVIER.
UH, HE DECODED THE LABELS.

30:34.123 --> 30:36.005
JAVIER?

30:36.005 --> 30:39.048
HE'S THIS MILLENNIAL COMPUTER
GENIUS FROM PRISON THAT I --

30:39.048 --> 30:40.129
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

30:40.129 --> 30:42.091
HE GOT OUT.
HE LANDED ON MY DOORSTEP.

30:42.091 --> 30:44.553
I DON'T KNOW.
HE LOOKS UP TO ME.

30:44.553 --> 30:47.556
LORD KNOWS WHY.

30:47.556 --> 30:51.560
I KNOW I'VE BEEN
A LITTLE DORMANT LATELY,

30:51.560 --> 30:53.352
BUT...I'VE STILL GOT
A LOT OF IDEAS.

30:53.352 --> 30:55.524
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
PROVE YOURSELF TO ME, NOLAN.

30:55.524 --> 30:59.688
I JUST HOPE YOU DIDN'T
TELL JAVIER TOO MUCH.

30:59.688 --> 31:02.902
OH, DON'T WORRY.

31:02.902 --> 31:06.906
HE HAD NO IDEA
WHAT WE WERE STEALING OR WHY.

31:06.906 --> 31:08.117
GOOD.

31:08.117 --> 31:10.369
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

31:10.369 --> 31:12.331
HEY, LOOK AT THIS.

31:18.497 --> 31:20.499
WOW.

31:20.499 --> 31:23.502
[ SCOFFS ]
THAT'S A BOMBSHELL.

31:23.502 --> 31:26.305
BUT WHO MADE THE BOMB?

31:28.467 --> 31:31.100
MY NEXT TARGET.

31:36.775 --> 31:39.188
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

31:39.188 --> 31:41.110
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

31:47.826 --> 31:50.990
HMM, WHY DON'T YOU PRACTICE
FOR THE SPOTLIGHT

31:50.990 --> 31:54.413
'CAUSE IT'S GONNA
KEEP GETTING HOTTER.

31:54.413 --> 31:57.997
CHARLOTTE, I HAVEN'T
SEEN YOU IN FOREVER.

31:57.997 --> 31:59.628
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:59.628 --> 32:02.751
I COVER VOULEZ' GOSSIP LINE NOW,
SO BUSY, BUSY.

32:02.751 --> 32:05.924
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN WE CAN'T
CATCH UP OVER LUNCH.
 OH, I'D LOVE THAT.

32:05.924 --> 32:07.306
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

32:07.306 --> 32:08.847
SEE WHAT I MEAN?
 [ BEEP ]

32:09.758 --> 32:13.432
PASCAL LeMARCHAL
JUST ARRIVED.
 HMM.

32:13.432 --> 32:15.814
I'LL INTRODUCE YOU.

32:15.814 --> 32:17.316
PASCAL.

32:17.316 --> 32:18.727
HI, CHARLOTTE.
HOW ARE YOU?

32:18.727 --> 32:19.979
[ SMOOCHING ]

32:19.979 --> 32:21.610
HAVE YOU MET MY SISTER-IN-LAW,
EMILY GRAYSON?

32:21.610 --> 32:22.821
HI. NICE TO MEET YOU.

32:27.116 --> 32:29.118
REALLY, YEAH.

32:29.118 --> 32:30.159
EXCUSE ME.

32:37.836 --> 32:39.838
I KNEW YOU
COULDN'T RESIST.

32:39.838 --> 32:42.791
WELL, FINE ART'S
MEANT TO BE DISPLAYED.

32:42.791 --> 32:43.752
AND APPRECIATED.

32:43.752 --> 32:45.884
KEEP YOUR DISTANCE,
PASCAL.

32:45.884 --> 32:49.888
THIS DRESS MAY TOUCH MY BODY,
BUT YOU'LL NEVER BE SO LUCKY.

32:54.683 --> 32:58.477
YOU LOOK HANDSOME,
MR. PORTER.

32:58.477 --> 32:59.938
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S A PLEASURE, MS. GRAYSON.

32:59.938 --> 33:02.481
"STEVIE," PLEASE.

33:02.481 --> 33:05.944
IT'S SO NICE TO MEET THE WOMAN
WHO'S MAKING MY SON SO HAPPY.

33:05.944 --> 33:07.316
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:07.316 --> 33:09.108
IF YOU'LL BOTH
EXCUSE ME.

33:09.108 --> 33:10.819
SURE.

33:10.819 --> 33:12.201
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

33:12.201 --> 33:14.073
AH. YOU MUST BE JACK.

33:14.073 --> 33:17.076
MR. LeMARCHAL,
IT'S SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

33:17.076 --> 33:19.668
I ALWAYS ENJOY MEETING
A FELLOW SELF-MADE MAN.

33:19.668 --> 33:21.710
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

33:21.710 --> 33:23.082
I'M IN TOWN
FOR A FEW MORE DAYS.

33:23.082 --> 33:25.714
HOPE WE CAN SPEND
SOME TIME TOGETHER.

33:25.714 --> 33:27.086
I WOULD LIKE THAT
VERY MUCH.

33:27.086 --> 33:28.837
[ TONE SOUNDS ]

33:28.837 --> 33:30.799
SHOULD WE, UH --
SHOULD WE FIND OUR SEATS?

33:30.799 --> 33:32.341
UM, I'LL JUST
BE A MOMENT.

33:32.341 --> 33:33.932
ALL RIGHT.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

33:33.932 --> 33:36.345
TAKE CARE.

33:36.345 --> 33:37.596
YES?

33:37.596 --> 33:39.768
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
LEAVING TOMORROW.

33:39.768 --> 33:41.100
OH, I MIGHT STAY
A LITTLE BIT LONGER

33:41.100 --> 33:43.732
TO HANDLE SOME
UNFINISHED BUSINESS.

33:43.732 --> 33:45.023
OH.

33:45.023 --> 33:48.147
AND MAYBE TEACH YOU A THING
OR TWO, SWEETHEART.

33:54.413 --> 33:56.615
EXCUSE ME.

33:56.615 --> 33:59.118
I'LL FILL YOU IN
ON EVERYTHING LATER,

33:59.118 --> 34:01.710
BUT IT'S TIME TO SHOW OUR
FATHERS WHAT WE'RE CAPABLE OF.

34:01.710 --> 34:03.252
CARE TO JOIN ME?

34:03.252 --> 34:08.377
I'M CERTAINLY
IN A FIGHTING MOOD.

34:08.377 --> 34:12.670
[ MAN SINGING IN ITALIAN ]

34:18.637 --> 34:19.848
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATES ]

34:25.893 --> 34:29.398
MOM.

34:29.398 --> 34:31.690
YOU ARE NOT
GONNA BELIEVE THIS.

34:31.690 --> 34:35.284
THIS JUST CAME
ACROSS THE VOULEZ TIP LINE.

34:37.406 --> 34:39.658
IT CAN'T BE TRUE,
CAN IT?

34:44.623 --> 34:45.964
HOW COULD YOU?

34:45.964 --> 34:47.666
I'M SORRY?

34:47.666 --> 34:50.668
FAKING A PREGNANCY
TO FORCE DANIEL INTO MARRIAGE.

34:50.668 --> 34:51.760
[ CROWD MURMURING ]

34:51.760 --> 34:53.051
WHAT KIND
OF LUNATIC ARE YOU?!

34:53.051 --> 34:55.974
[ SIGHS ]
YOU WANT TO DO THIS NOW?

34:55.974 --> 34:58.557
YOUR MEDICAL RECORDS
ARE OUT THERE.

34:58.557 --> 35:00.479
NOW EVERYONE KNOWS.

35:00.479 --> 35:03.562
THOSE ARE PRIVATE.
 SO IT'S TRUE?

35:03.562 --> 35:06.064
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

35:06.064 --> 35:07.856
WHERE ARE YOU GOING,
EMILY?!

35:10.989 --> 35:13.402
YOU CAN RUN EMILY,
BUT THIS WILL FOLLOW YOU.

35:13.402 --> 35:15.364
YOUR DIRTY,
LITTLE SECRET IS OUT.

35:15.364 --> 35:17.536
YOU'RE NOTHING
BUT A FRAUD AND A LIAR

35:17.536 --> 35:19.618
WHO DECEIVED MY SON
INTO MARRIAGE!

35:19.618 --> 35:22.581
EMILY THORNE,
YOU ARE DONE HERE.

35:22.581 --> 35:24.583
AFTER EVERYTHING I'VE DONE
TO PROTECT YOU, DANIEL.

35:24.583 --> 35:26.915
THIS IS OVER.

35:26.915 --> 35:28.587
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

35:28.587 --> 35:29.838
EMILY, DEAR,
IT'S TIME TO LEAVE.

35:29.838 --> 35:30.919
DON'T TOUCH ME!

35:32.421 --> 35:34.633
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

35:35.844 --> 35:38.307
[ MAN SOBBING OPERATICALLY ]

35:46.475 --> 35:47.856
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

35:47.856 --> 35:49.528
[ REPORTERS SHOUTING QUESTIONS ]

36:12.000 --> 36:13.632
THE DIVORCE PAPERS.

36:15.294 --> 36:16.755
I HAD THEM REDRAFTED,

36:16.755 --> 36:19.298
SO DON'T THINK THAT SETTLEMENT
AMOUNT IS STILL IN THERE.

36:19.298 --> 36:20.849
YOU'LL BE LEAVING
WITH NOTHING.

36:20.849 --> 36:24.473
WELL, I STILL HAVE THE FACT
THAT DANIEL SHOT ME.

36:24.473 --> 36:27.766
YOU CALLED A PRESS CONFERENCE,
GOT UP ON THAT BALCONY,

36:27.766 --> 36:30.769
AND TOLD THE WORLD
THAT LYDIA SHOT YOU.

36:30.769 --> 36:33.982
SO, WHICH STORY IS IT?
HMM?

36:33.982 --> 36:36.575
AFTER LAST NIGHT,
NO ONE'S GOING TO BELIEVE YOU.

36:36.575 --> 36:38.617
YOU'LL LOOK
LIKE A RESENTFUL WOMAN

36:38.617 --> 36:41.410
CAUGHT IN A LIE ABOUT
A PREGNANCY THAT NEVER EXISTED.

36:44.913 --> 36:48.707
THEN I GUESS YOU BOTH
GOT WHAT YOU WANTED.

36:51.330 --> 36:54.333
[ DOOR OPENS ]

36:58.387 --> 36:59.338
[ SIGHS ]

36:59.338 --> 37:01.550
OH,
I JUST LOVE THE OPERA.

37:01.550 --> 37:04.012
YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT PERFORMANCE
YOU'RE GOING TO GET.

37:04.012 --> 37:06.435
DID YOU LEAK
THE MEDICAL RECORDS?

37:06.435 --> 37:10.519
NO.
THE TIMING WAS CURIOUS.

37:10.519 --> 37:13.111
I LOVE YOU, DANIEL.

37:13.111 --> 37:16.695
AND I SIMPLY SAW AN OPPORTUNITY
TO HELP YOU, AND I TOOK IT,

37:16.695 --> 37:19.278
BUT I'M STILL KEEPING MY EYE
ON MS. THORNE.

37:19.278 --> 37:22.240
IF SHE STICKS AROUND,
YOUR THEORY'S CORRECT.

37:22.240 --> 37:23.862
SHE'S TARGETING US.

37:23.862 --> 37:26.204
AND I WILL
FIND OUT WHY.

37:29.708 --> 37:33.292
[ SCOFFS ]

37:33.292 --> 37:35.834
IF YOU GET SAUCE
ON MY COUCH,

37:35.834 --> 37:40.138
YOU'RE BUYING ME A NEW ONE,
AND, UH, I MEANT WHAT I SAID.

37:40.138 --> 37:43.342
YOU CAN STAY FOR ONE DAY,
WHICH IS OVER NOW.

37:43.342 --> 37:45.344
IS THAT ANY WAY
TO TREAT YOUR TECH SUPPORT?

37:45.344 --> 37:48.977
AND BESIDES, I CAN'T
 LEGALLY LEAVE ANYWAYS.

37:48.977 --> 37:51.350
I, UH...
[ SNIFFS ]

37:51.350 --> 37:53.942
I SORT OF GAVE MY PAROLE OFFICER
YOUR ADDRESS.

37:53.942 --> 37:57.316
YOU PUT YOURSELF UNDER
HOUSE ARREST AT MY HOUSE?

37:57.316 --> 37:59.358
[ SCOFFS ]

37:59.358 --> 38:03.161
I JUST WANT TO LIVE ALONE.
IS THAT TOO MUCH TO ASK?

38:03.161 --> 38:05.203
[ SIGHS ]

38:05.203 --> 38:08.537
IS THIS A...
IS THIS A PICTURE OF ME?

38:08.537 --> 38:10.959
YEAH, I'M, UH...

38:10.959 --> 38:12.501
I'M THINKING ABOUT
BECOMING AN ARTISTE.

38:12.501 --> 38:16.335
NOT ACCORDING
TO THESE SCRIBBLES, BUT...

38:16.335 --> 38:18.757
WAIT. WHAT IS THE REST
OF THIS, REALLY?

38:18.757 --> 38:20.509
IT'S AN IDEA
FOR A WEB AGGREGATOR.

38:20.509 --> 38:24.302
THINK OF IT
AS ANTISOCIAL MEDIA.

38:24.302 --> 38:26.975
I JUST...
CAN'T CRACK IT.

38:26.975 --> 38:28.977
THAT'S 'CAUSE
YOU'RE USING C++.

38:28.977 --> 38:31.560
I COULD FIX THIS
IN A NANOSECOND WITH BINARY.

38:31.560 --> 38:34.062
DO YOU SEE? THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.

38:34.062 --> 38:38.276
AND, SERIOUSLY,
THANKS FOR LETTING ME STAY, MAN.

38:38.276 --> 38:41.149
YOU'RE THE ONLY GUY I LIKED
INSIDE, SO I'M IN YOUR DEBT.

38:41.149 --> 38:45.654
WELL, BASED ON, UH,
WHAT I'M SEEING HERE...

38:47.746 --> 38:50.118
...YOU MIGHT BE ABLE
TO REPAY ME.

38:50.118 --> 38:51.329
[ SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

38:51.329 --> 38:53.121
[ BILLIARD BALLS CLACK ]

38:53.121 --> 38:55.954
Conrad: THE ONE TIME
I MISS THE OPERA,

38:55.954 --> 38:59.718
SOMETHING INTERESTING
ACTUALLY HAPPENS.

38:59.718 --> 39:02.721
IT WAS EXTRAORDINARY.

39:02.721 --> 39:04.803
I FEEL PRETTY BAD
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER-IN-LAW.

39:04.803 --> 39:08.226
OH, I'M SURE BY NOW,
SHE'S MY EX-DAUGHTER-IN-LAW.

39:08.226 --> 39:11.229
I WAS ON MY WAY OUT.

39:11.229 --> 39:14.733
PLEASE...FEEL FREE
TO DRINK ON MY TAB.

39:14.733 --> 39:16.144
NOW, PASCAL, COME ON.

39:16.144 --> 39:19.688
YOU AND I BOTH KNOW YOU'RE
GONNA GIVE ME WHAT I WANT.

39:19.688 --> 39:21.029
[ SIGHS ]

39:21.029 --> 39:26.114
CONRAD, I UNDERSTAND YOU
DON'T HEAR "NO" VERY OFTEN,

39:26.114 --> 39:31.329
BUT I HAVE NO INTENTION
OF MERGING OUR COMPANIES --

39:31.329 --> 39:33.161
EVER.

39:33.161 --> 39:37.546
WELL, WHAT IF I GOT YOU THE ONE
THING YOU'VE ALWAYS WANTED

39:37.546 --> 39:39.377
BUT NEVER HAD?

39:39.377 --> 39:42.501
I HAVE EVERYTHING A MAN
COULD WANT.

39:42.501 --> 39:45.053
EXCEPT VICTORIA.

39:50.929 --> 39:54.853
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

40:01.940 --> 40:03.111
HEY.

40:03.111 --> 40:05.734
HEY.

40:05.734 --> 40:07.526
I JUST WANTED TO
MAKE SURE YOU WERE OKAY.

40:07.526 --> 40:09.327
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

40:09.327 --> 40:11.700
PRESS IS SAYING
SOME PRETTY HARSH STUFF.

40:11.700 --> 40:12.871
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:12.871 --> 40:15.494
NO, I'M FINE.
EVERYTHING WENT AS EXPECTED.

40:15.494 --> 40:18.086
[ SCOFFS ]

40:18.086 --> 40:21.920
OF COURSE.
YOU WERE BEHIND IT.

40:21.920 --> 40:24.503
LOOK, AS MUCH AS I HATED
USING CHARLOTTE,

40:24.503 --> 40:26.505
I HAD TO CREATE A PUBLIC BREAK
FROM THE GRAYSONS,

40:26.505 --> 40:29.257
AND I NEEDED THEM
TO FEEL LIKE THEY WON.

40:29.257 --> 40:32.140
WHICH YOU WOULD ONLY DO
IF YOU HAD A NEW PLAN.

40:34.052 --> 40:35.814
TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

40:35.814 --> 40:39.057
YOU KNOW
HOW DANGEROUS THIS IS,

40:39.057 --> 40:40.939
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
GETTING HURT AGAIN.

40:40.939 --> 40:43.061
I'M NOT SITTING
ON THE SIDELINES ANYMORE, EMILY.

40:43.061 --> 40:44.483
WHAT YOU ARE DOING --

40:44.483 --> 40:47.486
IT'S NOT JUST ABOUT JUSTICE
FOR YOUR FATHER.

40:47.486 --> 40:49.698
IT'S ALSO FOR DECLAN...

40:49.698 --> 40:50.909
AND AMANDA.

40:50.909 --> 40:52.160
YES, AND I WILL
GET IT FOR THEM.

40:52.160 --> 40:54.573
I GOT YOU
THAT INFORMATION YESTERDAY,

40:54.573 --> 40:56.575
WHICH MEANS I'M NOW INVOLVED,
AND SO IS MY MOTHER.

40:56.575 --> 40:58.336
SO YOU CAN EITHER
MAKE THIS A FIGHT,

40:58.336 --> 41:01.039
OR YOU CAN GET GOOD
WITH IT NOW.

41:04.583 --> 41:06.715
WHAT WAS
ON THOSE DRIVES?

41:11.139 --> 41:13.552
[ SIGHS ]

41:13.552 --> 41:17.145
"CONRAD, PER YOU REQUEST,
I HANDLED TWM.

41:17.145 --> 41:20.478
YOUR DC PLAN IS SAFE."

41:20.478 --> 41:23.191
I ASSUME "DC's" YOUR DAD,
BUT WHAT'S -- WHAT'S "TWM"?

41:23.191 --> 41:25.023
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I'M GONNA FIGURE IT OUT.

41:25.023 --> 41:26.655
HOW?

41:26.655 --> 41:29.237
MY MOM SAID SHE NEVER KNEW
WHO WROTE THE LETTER.
 I THINK I DO.

41:29.237 --> 41:31.239
